Research shows saffron may be as effective as antidepressants for treating depression symptoms and could also boost sexual function, Dr. Daniel Amen shares.
President Donald Trump suggests McDonald's add more tartar sauce to the Filet-O-Fish during a recent speech, reigniting conversation about the iconic sandwich.
Researchers found that melting soft tau protein precursors before they form harmful fibrils could shift Alzheimer's treatment strategies toward early prevention.
President Trump claims title of first former McDonald's fry cook to become president after 30-minute campaign stint, joking he worked there longer than Kamala Harris ever did.
With over 32 million Americans facing food allergies, HHS Secretary RFK Jr. and FDA Chief Makary explore microbiome solutions. New gut health research may hold the key.
Scientists accidentally discovered how an old blood pressure drug hydralazine could fight aggressive brain cancer by targeting cellular oxygen sensors.
DoorDash's annual Cheeseburger Index reveals the most affordable cities for burger meals across 100 U.S. locations, with Lincoln, Nebraska, topping the list at $10.75.
Kraków tops new study as Europe's most stress-free city break destination. Quick 17-minute airport transfers, walkable UNESCO old town and affordable prices make it a great choice.
While teen smoking drops to under 3%, health experts fear pop culture revival could undo progress as 90% of long-term smokers start before age 18.
The viral TikTok potato bed trend promises better sleep by creating a cozy nest with pillows and blankets. A sleep expert shares benefits and potential risks.
Aspic and Jell-O salads are making a comeback on social media and in fine restaurants, as chefs reimagine retro gelatin dishes for modern palates.
Longevity expert Peter Attia breaks down different fiber types amid the trending '"fibermaxxing" movement. Learn how different fibers affect gut health, blood sugar and weight.
A fatal allergic reaction to red meat highlights a dangerous tick-borne illness. Researchers warn of alpha-gal syndrome risks from hamburgers and steak after tick exposure.
The Vatican officially rejected the Jesus apparitions reported in Dozulé, France, during the 1970s. The supernatural claims have been declared false after decades.
A viral TikTok hack with 3.7 million views reveals a simple trick to cook more at home. A Michigan woman claims it's helped her save at least $60 a week.
A new Gallup survey shows a dramatic 17-point drop in American adults valuing religion in their daily lives since 2015, with only 49% saying faith is important.
Mayo Clinic scientists have developed a new method to predict Alzheimer's risk decades before symptoms appear, using brain scans and genetics to estimate a 10-year likelihood.
Former vegan chef Mollie Engelhart made a shocking career pivot from running five Los Angeles vegan restaurants to becoming a Texas cattle rancher and advocate.
Gut health expert reveals why acid reflux is becoming a "silent epidemic" among men. Discover 7 simple steps to reduce symptoms and prevent complications.
Researchers say a new drug-delivery implant could help patients with hard-to-treat bladder cancer avoid losing their bladders — and stay cancer-free for years.
Green tea, walnuts and the Mankai plant may help slow brain aging, as a new study found that a green Mediterranean diet reduced a harmful protein linked to cognitive decline.
New research found that vitamin D3 therapy, aimed at achieving optimal blood levels, significantly reduced the risk of repeat heart attacks in certain cardiac patients.
New research suggests that coffee may actually help prevent atrial fibrillation recurrence after treatment, contradicting long-held warnings about caffeine.
After traveling to more than 60 countries, Swedish explorer Daniel Björnram shared what he’s learned about fear, kindness and the surprising generosity of people around the world.
Chronic kidney disease now ranks as the ninth leading cause of death globally, affecting 788 million people worldwide, according to major health study.
Bitter compounds in cocoa, berries and red wine may boost memory by 30% within an hour by triggering brain's alarm system, a new Japanese study reveals.
Dark showering is the latest wellness hack trending on social media. Learn how this simple routine can reduce anxiety and improve sleep, according to brain expert Dr. Daniel Amen.
Insurance data reveals dramatic regional differences in Ozempic and Mounjaro usage, with obesity-heavy states prescribing GLP-1 medications at triple the rate of others.
A new study reveals Americans are split on restaurant tipping. Thirty-four percent still tip 20%, while others give less than 10%, showing growing fatigue with tipping culture nationwide.
Notre Dame Cathedral in Paris, France, expects 12 million visitors this year as it approaches the anniversary of its reopening after the devastating April 2019 fire.
Taco Bell's electric-blue Mountain Dew Baja Blast pie is breaking the internet with its wild tropical lime flavor and shocking neon appearance that has fans divided.
Retro salad dressings like Catalina, Mayfair and celery seed are making a comeback as nostalgic home cooks revive these 1960s and '70s favorites.
Happiness expert and behavioral scientist Arthur Brooks reveals how workaholism destroys relationships and why excessive work is often used to escape negative emotions.
Longevity expert Dr. Peter Attia reveals why most people decline sharply in their 70s, and shares his athlete-inspired approach to healthy aging and fitness.
Heavy drinking is linked to strokes 11 years earlier than light drinkers, new study reveals. Three drinks daily may accelerate brain damage significantly, according to researchers.
TSA wait times surge to over two hours at some major airports during the government shutdown, with Houston, LAX and Orlando hit hard as travelers are urged to arrive early.
Oreo released experimental Thanksgiving dinner cookie flavors as part of its test-and-learn program, with a 12-pack collection selling out after one week online.
The government shutdown has triggered 1,000-plus flight delays as the FAA cuts capacity at 40 airports. Airlines are offering refunds and policy changes amid ongoing travel disruptions.
A new pancreatic cancer therapy targets sugar molecules on cell surfaces, offering hope where traditional immunotherapies have failed in treating this deadly disease.
A Starbucks holiday bear cup is going viral, and fans predict it will sell out in mere hours when the 2025 holiday menu launches with new and returning drinks.
New research reveals that weightlifting beats cardio for blood sugar control and diabetes prevention, as resistance training offers superior metabolic benefits.
Sleep experts reveal why going to bed after a certain time disrupts cortisol and melatonin balance, causing disrupted sleep. One doctor shares the optimal bedtime window.
A new study finds that eating 5 cups of fruits and vegetables daily can improve sleep quality by 16% in less than 24 hours, offering a natural solution for better rest.
A new study reveals that walking just 3,000 to 7,500 steps daily may delay Alzheimer's cognitive decline by up to seven years for at-risk adults.
Influencers face backlash for posting TikTok and Instagram videos while traveling to Jamaica during Category 5 Hurricane Melissa, with critics calling their content insensitive.
A new study reveals that melatonin supplements may increase heart failure risk by 90% in chronic insomnia patients, challenging assumptions about this popular sleep aid.
The FDA-approved drug Pluvicto offers hope for advanced prostate cancer patients, but access barriers remain despite proven effectiveness in extending survival.
A USC study reveals that blood pressure fluctuations between heartbeats may harm brain health even when overall readings are normal, potentially affecting memory in older adults.
A longevity expert reveals how immune systems begin aging after 35, making people more susceptible to infections and immune-related disorders over time.
Experts reveal the truth about CoQ10 supplements: safe for most, but not the miracle cure many believe. They advise on dosing, side effects and interactions.
A look at the top-trending stories in food, relationships, great outdoors and more.
